@sc{Cvs} 
(@pxref{Top,,, cvs, Concurrent Versions System})
is used to publish meta-data and to log operations 
performed on these files.
There is one @file{cvsroot} repository for each server one each host.
This repository handle one module for the local server's meta-data,
and one for each collection on ``master'' servers.
Remote servers access the ``master'' @sc{cvs} collection's repository
by using @procToolsSsh{}.
The @procToolsApache{} configuration files and the @process{Ssh}'s 
public keys are also distributed along servers using @sc{Cvs}.
The @sc{cvs} modules are setup by @procScriptsInitRemovePurge{} 
and @procScriptsNewFreeClean{} scripts.

